!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

meal /miːl/

(meals) 

1. N-COUNT A meal is an occasion when people sit down and eat, usually at a regular time. 一顿饭 

例： She sat next to him throughout the meal. 她在这一顿饭的时间里坐在他旁边。 

2. N-COUNT A meal is the food you eat during a meal. (一餐所吃的) 食物 

例： The waiter offered him red wine or white wine with his meal. 那位侍者为他的餐配了红葡萄酒或白葡萄酒。 

3. N-UNCOUNT the edible part of a grain or pulse (excluding wheat) ground to a coarse powder, used chiefly as animal food 动物饲料 

4. PHRASE If you have a square meal , you have a large, healthy meal. 丰盛的一餐 

例： The troops are very tired. They haven't had a square meal for four or five days. 这些部队非常疲惫。他们已经四五天没有丰盛食物了。

</div>

